The paper proposes a method for training Q-functions for MDPs with a given LTL property, which involves the use of neural networks and reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with control policies and synthesising them, which suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions constructing an automaton and defining an adaptive reward function, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with logic and temporal properties, which suggests that it could also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
